======================================================================
PART 3: DENDRIFORM ALGEBRAS — KEY1 OPERATIONS
======================================================================
Free dendriform algebra (KEY1=2 operations):
  dim_n = Catalan(n)
  n=1: dim = 1
  n=2: dim = 2
  n=3: dim = 5
  n=4: dim = 14
  n=5: dim = 42
  n=6: dim = 132
  n=7: dim = 429

Free tridendriform algebra (KEY2=3 operations):
  dim_n = (n+1)^{n-1} (parking functions)
  n=1: dim = 1
  n=2: dim = 3
  n=3: dim = 16
  n=4: dim = 125
  n=5: dim = 1296
  n=6: dim = 16807
  n=7: dim = 262144

Rooted trees (pre-Lie algebra):
  n=1: labeled rooted trees = 1
  n=2: labeled rooted trees = 2
  n=3: labeled rooted trees = 9
  n=4: labeled rooted trees = 64
  n=5: labeled rooted trees = 625
  n=6: labeled rooted trees = 7776
  n=7: labeled rooted trees = 117649

Tridendriform/Dendriform ratio:
  n=1: 1/1 = 1.0000
  n=2: 3/2 = 1.5000
  n=3: 16/5 = 3.2000
  n=4: 125/14 = 8.9286
  n=5: 1296/42 = 30.8571
  n=6: 16807/132 = 127.3258
  n=7: 262144/429 = 611.0583

======================================================================
PART 4: HOPF ALGEBRA STRUCTURE
======================================================================
Tournament Hopf algebra coproduct:
At n=3, 2 iso classes: cyclic (C3) and transitive (T3)
  Δ(T3) = T3⊗1 + 1⊗T3 + 3*(T2⊗T1)
    where T2 = unique tournament on 2 vertices, T1 = single vertex
  Δ(C3) = C3⊗1 + 1⊗C3 + 3*(T2⊗T1)
  (Both have same coproduct terms — same vertex subsets!)
  Primitive part: C3 - T3 is primitive if sub-tournament terms cancel
  But they're the same → C3 - T3 IS primitive!

Tournament iso classes (A000568): [1, 1, 1, 2, 4, 12, 56, 456]
Primitive dimensions (Euler transform inverse):

