PART 5: TOURNAMENT SPECIES EGF
======================================================================
Tournament species EGF: T(x) = Σ 2^C(n,2) x^n/n!
  n=0: 2^0/0! = 1/1 = 1.000000
  n=1: 2^0/1! = 1/1 = 1.000000
  n=2: 2^1/2! = 2/2 = 1.000000
  n=3: 2^3/3! = 8/6 = 1.333333
  n=4: 2^6/4! = 64/24 = 2.666667
  n=5: 2^10/5! = 1024/120 = 8.533333
  n=6: 2^15/6! = 32768/720 = 45.511111
  n=7: 2^21/7! = 2097152/5040 = 416.101587

H-weighted species: H(x) = Σ (Σ_T H(T)) x^n/n!
  n=1: Σ H(T) = 1, coeff = 1.0000 = 2^0
  n=2: Σ H(T) = 2, coeff = 1.0000 = 2^0
  n=3: Σ H(T) = 12, coeff = 2.0000 = 2^1
  n=4: Σ H(T) = 192, coeff = 8.0000 = 2^3
  n=5: Σ H(T) = 7680, coeff = 64.0000 = 2^6
  n=6: Σ H(T) = 737280, coeff = 1024.0000 = 2^10
  n=7: Σ H(T) = 165150720, coeff = 32768.0000 = 2^15

H²-weighted species: Σ_T H(T)² = ?
  n=3: mean_H = 3/2 = 1.5000, N = 8
  n=4: mean_H = 3 = 3.0000, N = 64
  n=5: mean_H = 15/2 = 7.5000, N = 1024
  n=6: mean_H = 45/2 = 22.5000, N = 32768

======================================================================
PART 6: OPERAD COMPOSITION — TOURNAMENTS AS OPERATIONS
======================================================================
Tournament operad structure:
  T ∘_i T' = replace vertex i of T with tournament T'
  H(T ∘_i T') = H(T) * H(T')  when inter-block transitive
  This makes H a 'multiplicative character' of the tournament operad!

Operad composition examples:
  C₃ ∘ (T₁, T₁, T₁) = C₃ itself, H = 3
  T₃ ∘ (T₁, T₁, T₁) = T₃ itself, H = 1
  C₃ ∘ (C₃, C₃, C₃) = block-transitive with blocks of size 3
    H should be 3 * 3 * 3 * 3 = 81... wait, H(outer)*∏H(inner)
    H = H(C₃) * H(C₃)³ = 3 * 27 = 81
    BUT this requires the inter-block ordering to follow C₃
    The block-transitive formula needs TRANSITIVE inter-block
    So: T₃ ∘ (C₃, C₃, C₃) gives H = 1 * 3³ = 27 = 3³
    And: C₃ substitution is NOT covered by THM-1237 (non-transitive)

======================================================================
PART 7: SCHRÖDER, MOTZKIN, AND TOURNAMENT NUMBERS
======================================================================
Motzkin numbers: [1, 1, 2, 4, 9, 21, 51, 127, 323, 835]
  M_4 = 9 = 3² = KEY2²
  M_5 = 21 = 3*7 = KEY2*H_forb_1  ← FORBIDDEN H at n=6!
  M_6 = 51 = 3*17
  M_7 = 127 = 2^7 - 1 (Mersenne prime!)

Large Schröder numbers: [1, 2, 6, 22, 90, 394, 1806, 8558]
  S_0 = 1, S_1 = 2 = KEY1, S_2 = 6 = h(G2)
  S_3 = 22 = 2*11
  S_4 = 90 = 2*3²*5

Small Schröder numbers: [1, 1, 3, 11, 45, 197, 903, 4279]
  s_2 = 3 = KEY2
  s_3 = 11 = next prime after 7
  s_4 = 45 = max H at n=6!!
  s_5 = 197 (prime)

*** CROWN JEWEL: max_H(6) = 45 = small Schröder number s_4! ***
    Also: s_4 = 45 = 9*5 = 3²*5 = KEY2²*KEY_SUM

