PART 8: BALLOT NUMBERS AND LATTICE PATHS
======================================================================
Narayana numbers N(n,k):
  n=1: [1], sum = 1 = C_1
  n=2: [1, 1], sum = 2 = C_2
  n=3: [1, 3, 1], sum = 5 = C_3
  n=4: [1, 6, 6, 1], sum = 14 = C_4
  n=5: [1, 10, 20, 10, 1], sum = 42 = C_5
  n=6: [1, 15, 50, 50, 15, 1], sum = 132 = C_6

Notable Narayana values:
  N(3,2) = 3 = KEY2
  N(4,2) = 6 = h(G2)
  N(5,2) = 10 = triangular_4
  N(5,3) = 20 = C(6,3)

